    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Lancaster</placeName>
                <date>May 28th 1857</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>Respected Sir<lb/> We have<lb/> the frankness of directing a few<lb/> lines to you
                hoping they will receive<lb/> your notice. Being informed that<lb/> your
                Congregation have contemplated<lb/> to erect a new house of worship<lb/>
                <sic>wich</sic> is to be <sic>handsomly</sic> finished,<lb/> we have made it an
                object of<lb/> inquiry to <sic>asertain</sic> from you,<lb/>
                <sic>wherter</sic> your intention is to have<lb/> any decorative painting
                executed<lb/> at the interior walls &amp; ceilings of it,<lb/> and
                    <sic>wherter</sic> that part of the work<lb/> has been <sic>allready</sic>
                awarded to some<lb/> person or not? If not, will you<lb/> please and inform us!__.
                We are<lb/> anxious to give you a proposal,<lb/> and would politely request you
                to<lb/> pardon our boldness (as <sic>perhapps</sic><lb/> entire strangers to you) in
                introduce_<lb/>ing <sic>ourselfs</sic> as Decorative Painters<lb/> in Fresco,
                Encaustic and oil colours,</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>Twenty years practical experience<lb/> (with many <sic>recomendations</sic> of
                the<lb/> most trustworthy men from all<lb/> parts of this and adjoining states)<lb/>
                warrants us in saying that, we are<lb/> able to execute painting entrusted<lb/> to
                us, in a <sic>maner</sic> not to be<lb/>
                <sic>exceded</sic>, and <sic>supscribe</sic>
                <sic>ourselfs</sic> as<lb/> Respectfully Yours</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Geo. &amp; John J. Seiling</persName>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
